Subject: Re: windshield wiper woes...


I had the exact same problem a year ago...

 From your description, I'd imagine the best thing to do is this:

First, remove the glove compartment.  Then move the nuts on the inside 
of the wiper shaft back enough so you pull back on the wiper pivot from 
the inside, giving yourself enough of the shaft so's you can hacksaw it 
off.  Then just slide the shaft out the front of the bus.

I'm pretty sure Joe at bustedbus.com sells all the replacement parts you 
might need...

And hey, just be glad it wasn't the driver's side wiper - now THAT'S a pain!

Paul Sinfield
